## flexbox is one dimentional method for arranging the content.
you ceate div .
inside div everything will be separate and some of are in next line .
by using flex you will arragne it in one collom or one row

for expample:
html:
<div class="container">
  <div>Box 1</div>
  <div>Box 2</div>
  <div>Box 3</div>
</div>

css:
.container {
  display: flex;
}

##now try some of flex elements

1.flex-direction:
its use for giving vertical or horizentan direction 
.container {
  flex-direction: row;                                      /* default */
  flex-direction: column;                                 /* vertical */
}


2.justify-content:
its use for giving space horizental.

.container {
  justify-content: center;                  /* center */
  justify-content: space-between;               
  justify-content: space-around;
  justify-content: space-evenly;
  }

3.align-item:
it use for aligning items like in top middle or buttom in vertical.

.container {
  align-items: center;                              /* middle vertically */
  align-items: flex-start;
  align-items: flex-end;
}

4.gap :
it use for giving gap 

.container {
  gap: 20px;
}

^^imp: if you use flex all item will try to settle forcefully thats why you can warp tham

5.flex-wrap:
use for not shirnk and move to the next line

.container {
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}









